            {
              "label": "The Story",
              "type": "backstory",
              "content": "Cutlets  can be a tea time snack or a short eat, as we call it, that can be eaten on the go or accompanied by other similar food at a tea party, or even at a special lunch or dinner table. \nThis snack is another remnant of the colonial influence on our food, resembling the British croquettes."
            },
            {
              "label": "What You'll Need",
              "type": "ingredients",
              "content": "Ingredients:\n- 500 grams of mackerel or tuna fish from a can, or fresh fish boiled with salt and pepper, de-boned and crushed\n- Three large potatoes boiled, peeled, and mashed\n- One large red onion, finely chopped\n- Three sprigs of curry leaves, finely chopped\n- Three teaspoons of freshly ground pepper\n- Half a lemon juice\n- Salt\n- Fine breadcrumbs\n- Oil for deep frying\n- Batter made with all-purpose flour, salt, and some water (consistency of thin crepes)",
