            {
              "label": "How to Make It",
              "type": "preparation",
              "content": "Preparing the Fish and Potatoes\n\n1. Boil and mash the potatoes, then set them aside.\n2. Drain the fish and mash it with a fork, then set it aside.\n\nMaking the Filling\n\n1. Heat two tablespoons of oil in a pan.\n2. Saute the finely cut onions, curry leaves, cardamom, and cinnamon powder.\n3. Add the mashed fish and mix well.\n4. Add pepper and salt to taste.\n5. Turn off the heat and add the boiled, mashed potato, mixing well.\n6. Add more salt and pepper to taste if needed.\n7. Add the lemon juice.\n\nShaping and Coating\n\n1. Once the mixture is cool, shape it into little balls, about the size of a golf ball.\n2. Coat the balls in a thin consistency batter.\n3. Coat them in breadcrumbs.\n4. If you are frying them immediately, coat the cutlets again in breadcrumbs to get a good covering.\n\nCooking the Cutlets\n\n1. Heat the oil in a pan for deep frying.\n2. Deep fry the cutlets, turning them gently.\n3. Do not overcrowd them, as they may tend to crack.\n4. Be gentle when turning them over.\n5. Drain in a colander with some paper.\n6. Alternatively, coat the cutlets with oil using a pastry brush and fry them in an air fryer on a suitable setting.",
