            {
              "label": "The Story",
              "type": "backstory",
              "content": " lamprai is a dish from the Dutch Burgher community of Sri Lanka. The name comes from the Dutch word, lompregist, which means parcel of food. I have looked at a few recipes and have come out with my own version of lamprai.\n\nSo the main items going into the rice packet wrapped in a banana leaf consists of ghee rice, mixed meat curry, ash plantain curry, and my substitute is frozen chip curry because we can't find ash plantains here often. Frikadelas, or Danish meatballs . it's a staple in their cuisine. Blachan and eggplant pehi or batu mojo. So the first thing to be done is the meat curry."
            },
            {
